    "description": {
      "value": "<p>Soldiers are specialized in pure, focused combat abilities and are deadly with their firearms.</p>\n<ul>\n<li><strong>Hit Die:&nbsp;</strong>d10</li>\n<li><strong>Primary Ability:&nbsp;</strong>Strength OR Dexterity</li>\n<li><strong>Saves:&nbsp;</strong>Strength &amp; Dexterity</li>\n</ul>\n<h4 id=\"weapon-of-choice\" style=\"-webkit-print-color-adjust: exact; box-sizing: border-box; border: 0px; font-variant-numeric: inherit; font-variant-east-asian: inherit; font-weight: 800; font-stretch: inherit; font-size: 0.458cm; line-height: inherit; font-family: MrJeeves; vertical-align: baseline; margin-top: 0.2em; margin-bottom: 0px; color: #58180d;\">Weapon of Choice</h4>\n<p style=\"-webkit-print-color-adjust: exact; box-sizing: border-box; border: 0px; font-variant-numeric: inherit; font-variant-east-asian: inherit; font-stretch: inherit; font-size: 11.9811px; line-height: 1.3em; font-family: BookSanity; vertical-align: baseline; margin-top: 0px; margin-bottom: 0px; padding: 0px 0px 0.8em; z-index: 15; break-inside: avoid;\">By 3rd level, you have undergone extensive training with a single weapon type. Choose a weapon type which becomes your Weapon of Choice. When you are holding your Weapon of Choice you gain a set of abilities that are fueled by special dice called superiority dice. You may spend 1 month of intensive training to exchange your Weapon of Choice with another weapon type.</p>\n<p style=\"-webkit-print-color-adjust: exact; box-sizing: border-box; border: 0px; font-variant-numeric: inherit; font-variant-east-asian: inherit; font-stretch: inherit; font-size: 11.9811px; line-height: 1.3em; font-family: BookSanity; vertical-align: baseline; margin-top: -0.8em; margin-bottom: 0px; padding: 0px 0px 0.8em; z-index: 15; break-inside: avoid; text-indent: 1em;\"><strong style=\"-webkit-print-color-adjust: exact; box-sizing: border-box; border: 0px; font-style: inherit; font-variant: inherit; font-stretch: inherit; font-size: inherit; line-height: inherit; font-family: inherit; vertical-align: baseline; margin: 0px; padding: 0px; letter-spacing: 0.03em;\">Superiority Dice</strong>: You have four superiority dice, which are d8s. A superiority die is expended when you use it. You regain all of your expended superiority dice when you finish a short or long rest.</p>\n<p style=\"-webkit-print-color-adjust: exact; box-sizing: border-box; border: 0px; font-variant-numeric: inherit; font-variant-east-asian: inherit; font-stretch: inherit; font-size: 11.9811px; line-height: 1.3em; font-family: BookSanity; vertical-align: baseline; margin-top: -0.8em; margin-bottom: 0px; padding: 0px 0px 0.8em; z-index: 15; break-inside: avoid; text-indent: 1em;\">You can expend superiority dice to gain a number of different benefits:</p>\n<ul style=\"-webkit-print-color-adjust: exact; box-sizing: border-box; border: 0px; font-variant-numeric: inherit; font-variant-east-asian: inherit; font-stretch: inherit; font-size: 11.9811px; line-height: 1.3em; font-family: BookSanity; vertical-align: baseline; margin-top: 0px; margin-bottom: 0.8em; padding-left: 1.4em; list-style-position: outside; list-style-image: initial;\">\n<li style=\"-webkit-print-color-adjust: exact; box-sizing: border-box; border: 0px; font: inherit; vertical-align: baseline; margin: 0px; padding: 0px; break-inside: avoid;\">When you make a weapon attack against a creature with your Weapon of Choice, you can expend one superiority die to add it to the attack roll. You can use this ability before or after making the attack roll, but before any of the effects of the attack are applied.</li>\n<li style=\"-webkit-print-color-adjust: exact; box-sizing: border-box; border: 0px; font: inherit; vertical-align: baseline; margin: 0px; padding: 0px; break-inside: avoid;\">When you damage a creature with a weapon attack from your Weapon of Choice, you can expend one superiority die to add it to the damage roll. You can use this ability after rolling damage. If the attack causes the target to make a Constitution saving throw to maintain concentration, it has disadvantage on that save.</li>\n<li style=\"-webkit-print-color-adjust: exact; box-sizing: border-box; border: 0px; font: inherit; vertical-align: baseline; margin: 0px; padding: 0px; break-inside: avoid;\">When you are hit by a melee attack, if you are currently holding your Weapon of Choice, you can expend one superiority die as a reaction, adding the number rolled to your AC. If the attack still hits, you take half damage from it.</li>\n</ul>\n<h4 id=\"strafe\" style=\"-webkit-print-color-adjust: exact; box-sizing: border-box; border: 0px; font-variant-numeric: inherit; font-variant-east-asian: inherit; font-weight: 800; font-stretch: inherit; font-size: 0.458cm; line-height: inherit; font-family: MrJeeves; vertical-align: baseline; margin-top: 0.2em; margin-bottom: 0px; color: #58180d;\">Strafe</h4>\n<p style=\"-webkit-print-color-adjust: exact; box-sizing: border-box; border: 0px; font-variant-numeric: inherit; font-variant-east-asian: inherit; font-stretch: inherit; font-size: 11.9811px; line-height: 1.3em; font-family: BookSanity; vertical-align: baseline; margin-top: 0px; margin-bottom: 0px; padding: 0px 0px 0.8em; z-index: 15; break-inside: avoid;\">At 7th level, when you take the Dash or Disengage action, you can make 1 weapon attack with your Weapon of Choice as a bonus action at any point during your movement.</p>\n<h4 id=\"weapon-of-choice\" style=\"-webkit-print-color-adjust: exact; box-sizing: border-box; border: 0px; font-variant-numeric: inherit; font-variant-east-asian: inherit; font-weight: 800; font-stretch: inherit; font-size: 0.458cm; line-height: inherit; font-family: MrJeeves; vertical-align: baseline; margin-top: 0.2em; margin-bottom: 0px; color: #58180d;\">Weapon of Choice</h4>\n<p style=\"-webkit-print-color-adjust: exact; box-sizing: border-box; border: 0px; font-variant-numeric: inherit; font-variant-east-asian: inherit; font-stretch: inherit; font-size: 11.9811px; line-height: 1.3em; font-family: BookSanity; vertical-align: baseline; margin-top: 0px; margin-bottom: 0px; padding: 0px 0px 0.8em; z-index: 15; break-inside: avoid;\">You gain another superiority die (5 total) at 10th level and the die type becomes a d10.</p>\n<h4 id=\"devastating-critical\" style=\"-webkit-print-color-adjust: exact; box-sizing: border-box; border: 0px; font-variant-numeric: inherit; font-variant-east-asian: inherit; font-weight: 800; font-stretch: inherit; font-size: 0.458cm; line-height: inherit; font-family: MrJeeves; vertical-align: baseline; margin-top: 0.2em; margin-bottom: 0px; color: #58180d;\">Devastating Critical</h4>\n<p style=\"-webkit-print-color-adjust: exact; box-sizing: border-box; border: 0px; font-variant-numeric: inherit; font-variant-east-asian: inherit; font-stretch: inherit; font-size: 11.9811px; line-height: 1.3em; font-family: BookSanity; vertical-align: baseline; margin-top: 0px; margin-bottom: 0px; padding: 0px 0px 0.8em; z-index: 15; break-inside: avoid;\">Starting at the 15th level, when you score a critical hit with your Weapon of Choice, you gain a bonus to that weapon's damage roll equal to your soldier level.</p>\n<h4 id=\"weapon-of-choice\" style=\"-webkit-print-color-adjust: exact; box-sizing: border-box; border: 0px; font-variant-numeric: inherit; font-variant-east-asian: inherit; font-weight: 800; font-stretch: inherit; font-size: 0.458cm; line-height: inherit; font-family: MrJeeves; vertical-align: baseline; margin-top: 0.2em; margin-bottom: 0px; color: #58180d;\">Weapon of Choice</h4>\n<p style=\"-webkit-print-color-adjust: exact; box-sizing: border-box; border: 0px; font-variant-numeric: inherit; font-variant-east-asian: inherit; font-stretch: inherit; font-size: 11.9811px; line-height: 1.3em; font-family: BookSanity; vertical-align: baseline; margin-top: 0px; margin-bottom: 0px; padding: 0px 0px 0.8em; z-index: 15; break-inside: avoid;\">You gain another superiority die (6 total) at 18th level and the die type becomes a d12.</p>",
